Date: Sat, 18 Apr 2026 08:42:56 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Phase: Upgrade Shop UI + Optics Visual Polish + QA

Phase 1 - Upgrade Shop UI & Loadout:
- Extend WeaponPartCatalog: Rifle/Ammo/Cosmetic categories, WeaponPartRarity, description/icon/requiresContractIds/opticsTierIndex on parts, zoomMultiplier/swayMultiplier/noiseRadiusMultiplier/magazineSizeDelta on modifiers
- Extend PlayerProgress: seenPartIds, completedContractIds, selectedAmmoId
- Extend PlayerProgressUpgrades: HasSeenPart/MarkPartSeen, HasCompletedContract/MarkContractCompleted, GetSelectedAmmoId/SetSelectedAmmoId
- Add RuntimeLoadout: immutable per-mission snapshot built by GameManager
- Rewrite UpgradeShopController: dynamic category tabs, item list, stat preview (current vs with part), buy/equip with human-readable errors, auto-pellet refresh, NEW badges
- Add ShopItemButton for per-item prefab
- MainMenuController: Shop button/panel, null-safe button wiring
- GameManager: builds CurrentRuntimeLoadout before missions, records completed contractIds into PlayerProgress, exposes WeaponPartCatalog

Phase 2 - Optics Visual Polish (URP):
- Add ScopeVolumeProfileSet: maps ScopeMode -> VolumeProfile + reticle sprite/color + HUD accent + rat eye-shine
- Extend OpticsTierConfig: per-tier supportedScopeModes, min/max FOV, swayMultiplier, aimAssistConeMultiplier, TryGetTier/SupportsMode
- Rewrite ScopeOverlayController: URP Volume swapping, per-mode reticle + HUD accent tint, CurrentScopeMode + static OnScopeModeChanged event, CycleMode/EnforceSupportedMode
- Add RatEyeShine: per-rat emissive driver subscribing to scope mode events
- WeaponController: applies per-tier sway / aim-assist on top of equipped-part modifiers, captures aim-assist base once, CycleScopeMode helper

Phase 3 - QA:
- PHASE2-NOTES.md at repo root documenting new/changed scripts, required inspector wiring, per-scene steps, TODOs

All changes are additive/backward-compatible. No .asset, .prefab or .unity files modified. Namespaces preserved. Unity 2023 LTS + URP.
